import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.gca()
    ax.hist(data['delay'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    ax.xaxis.set_tick_params(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.subplot(111)
    ax.boxplot(data['distance'].dropna(), vert=False)
    plt.xlabel('Distance (miles)')
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='ignore')
    origin_counts = data['origin'].value_counts()
    top_20_origin_counts = origin_counts[:20]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax.bar(top_20_origin_counts.index, top_20_origin_counts.values)
    ax.set_title('What is the most common origin airport?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Origin Airport')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['distance'], data['delay'], alpha=0.5)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='ignore')
    data['day_of_week'] = data['date'].dt.day_name()
    day_counts = data['day_of_week'].value_counts()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax.bar(day_counts.index, day_counts.values)
    ax.set_title('What is the busiest day of the week for flights?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Day of the Week')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
